{"word":"ἐξανθέω","slug":"ἐξανθέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξανθέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to put out flowers</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to burst forth</i>, like an efflorescence, <i>bloom forth</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—of ulcers, <i>to break out</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}